  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti. The monsoon is just starting and I already miss the sound of rain on tin roofs. What’s on your mind today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Reading. Need to. No energy for anything else. Papers coming up. 😣"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Need to\" sounds like a heavy phrase. Papers ahead can drain the joy out of anything. What book are you trying to get through?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Not a book. Notes. Revising for NEET PG. So much to do, so little time. I feel like I'll never be ready. 🤕"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That weight of \"never being ready\" before big exams is real — it’s part of the phase. What one small step feels doable right now?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maybe 1 chapter. Or notes for 1 topic. But even that feels like a mountain. 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "The \"mountain\" feeling is normal when the goal feels far. What topic is on your list first — just the name?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Pharmacology. Always starts with that. But today, even opening the notes feels like chya... I don’t know, a struggle. 🤷‍♀️"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Opening pharmacology notes when energy is low is a struggle — it asks a lot. What helps you take that first step, even a tiny one?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Coffee. And a playlist. But even that feels like work. I just wanna slump. 🥱"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Coffee and a playlist are good tools — but when even using them feels like effort, the slump wins. What small thing could feel like a win instead?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "10 mins of notes. If I just sit and do 10 mins, maybe it won’t feel so bad. But getting up... laaaazy. 😴"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"10 mins\" is a smart way to trick the brain into starting. The getting-up part is the real hurdle. What helps you beat the \"just five more minutes\" trap?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Alarm on silent. And a friend who texts. Otherwise, bed is like a trap. 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "An alarm on silent and a friend’s text — clever moves to escape the bed. What’s the first thing you do once you’re up and out?"
    }
  ],
